{
  "answer": "**In Allama Iqbal's poem \"Subah Ka Sitara\" (\"Morning Star\" or \"The Star of the Dawn\") from *Bang-e-Dara Part 1*, the speaker is Venus personified—the herald of dawn, appearing before sunrise.**[^1]\n\nVenus laments its exalted yet burdensome celestial fate: it would \"forsake the joy of sun and moon\" to escape its duty as the morning's herald, finding \"this starry realm holds no delight\" and preferring \"earth's lowliness than this great height.\" It describes the sky as \"the void's abyss,\" itself confined to a \"dawn's rent shroud\" where it must \"daily die and live,\" drinking the \"morning-draught that Death's hands give.\" This \"service\" and \"honor\" seem worthless compared to a \"dark, silent fate.\"[^2]\n\n**The speaker yearns for earthly incarnation over its starry existence**, wishing instead to be a pearl in ocean depths (leaving the sea to adorn a throat), a jewel on a queen's crown, a stone on Solomon's ring, dew on a flower, spangles on a forehead, or—most poignantly—a tear from the eye of a wife whose armored husband departs for battle in defense of the homeland. There, amid \"hope and deep despair,\" it would find \"eternal life\" in the dust, igniting \"the fire of love to all mankind.\"[^3]\n\n**Iqbal uses Venus's voice to contrast hollow cosmic splendor with the profound, self-sacrificing vitality of human passion and earthly bonds.**\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, \"Subah Ka Sitara\" [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/42-subah-ka-sitara/translation/#p-aab796).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, \"Subah Ka Sitara\" [passage](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/42-subah-ka-sitara/translation/#p-aab796 \"p-aab796 p-658448 p-ec866d p-f7ffd9 p-17be48\").\n\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, \"Subah Ka Sitara\" [passage](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/42-subah-ka-sitara/translation/#p-69f75f \"p-69f75f p-a38930 p-4accfe p-ce41ff p-3abca5 p-e76893 p-f560c9 p-ea5c34 p-4d2e45 p-8594f9 p-fed550 p-b43666 p-aa7dc1 p-5fd53a p-2aceb1\").",
